# API design standards (no exceptions)

When adding or changing API endpoints or frontend API calls, follow **`docs/API_DESIGN_STANDARDS.md`**.

- **REST**: Resource URLs, correct HTTP methods (GET/POST/PUT-PATCH/DELETE). Deletes are `DELETE /api/resource/{id}`; backend performs all related deletes.
- **Layers**: Router → Service → Transaction. No business logic or SQL in routers.
- **One call per use case**: Frontend does not chain generic "delete by query" or table endpoints to implement a business flow; backend exposes one purpose-built endpoint (e.g. `DELETE /api/buildings/{building_number}`) that does the full operation.
- **Errors**: `HTTPException` with appropriate status and `detail`; no raw DB/stack in responses.
- **Auth**: Use the same auth pattern (e.g. `Depends(get_current_user)`) on all protected routes.

Generic data endpoints (e.g. GET/POST on `/api/data/{table}`) are for read/generic use only; app features use resource-specific endpoints.
